    <div class="panel-body">

        <p class="contentp">

            Toronto is the largest city in Canada in terms of population. It is the centre of business, finanace, arts and culture worldwide. The city is located on Lake Ontario.

            As of the 2011 census, the population of Toronto is 2,615,060 with a metropolitan population of 5,583,064. The city was founded in 1793

            and was named York until it's incorporation in 1834 as Toronto. In 1998, Toronto was mergered with East York, Etobicoke, North York, Scarborough, and York to become a single city.
            <br /><br />
            The city was named after the Prince Frederick, Duke of York and Albany by Governor John Graves Simcoe. In Toronto, the area codes

            are 416, 647 and 437.
        </p>
